  "texts": [
    "An auto topology pass expands this high-level specification into explicit draft and target device pools with fully defined network connections, enabling rapid system configuration and large-scale parameter sweeps.",
    "The core DSD scheduler leverages SimPy to model draft and target servers as concurrent processes, each with explicit queues for batch formation and request scheduling.",
    "Network links are represented as delay elements associated with send and receive events, parameterized by configurable RTT and jitter.",
    "This request-level abstraction allows fast exploration of large design spaces while preserving accuracy in modeling system-level queueing and network dynamics.",
    "To accurately capture per-kernel execution latency without reimplementing low-level GPU models, DSD-Sim incorporates a hardware performance modeling engine based on VIDUR (Agrawal et al., 2024b)."
  ],
